and you shake it and spray.

22:37.013 --> 22:39.190
- So if you had to guess,
till it's done,

22:39.274 --> 22:43.027
just give me an educated guess.
It doesn't have to be perfect.

22:43.111 --> 22:46.688
- It'll be done maybe
two months.

22:46.773 --> 22:48.107
- That is
so much better than a year

22:48.191 --> 22:50.785
and six months or two years
and six months.

22:50.869 --> 22:54.121
- This will be a quick,
fun project that's different.

22:54.280 --> 22:55.781
- I love it.
- Cool.

22:55.865 --> 22:57.282
- Thanks, Bob.
- All right, I'm going to have

22:57.376 --> 22:58.700
the guys strip it
when they get back from lunch.

22:58.794 --> 23:00.285
- All right, I appreciate it.

23:00.379 --> 23:01.870
- And I'll just look at this
for a little bit more.

23:01.955 --> 23:03.205
- You know what we could do?

23:03.298 --> 23:05.124
Let's throw this in my Cadillac,

23:05.208 --> 23:06.792
and then we'll take the engine
and transmission

23:06.876 --> 23:09.553
out of my Cadillac,
but it won't fit in that.

23:09.712 --> 23:11.389
- Well, they already got
an anchor in that.

23:11.548 --> 23:14.383
- I get it, man,
but that sure is gorgeous.

23:14.467 --> 23:15.968
- Man,
I can't wait to fire you up...

23:16.061 --> 23:17.719
- [laughs]

23:17.804 --> 23:19.980
- Drive you down the street.
- You're talking to it.

23:20.065 --> 23:21.640
- You got to be nice
to them, Kevin.

23:21.733 --> 23:23.901
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:28.064 --> 23:34.412
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:37.657 --> 23:38.999
- Ry.
- Yo.

23:39.084 --> 23:42.828
- Oh, man, there you are.
That's cool.

23:42.912 --> 23:44.913
Whoo. Look at this color.

23:44.998 --> 23:46.924
- Our client, Butch,
wants one of my favorite colors

23:47.083 --> 23:48.834
for his Iron Horse,
black cherry,

23:48.918 --> 23:51.095
heavy on the cherry,
light on the black.

23:51.179 --> 23:54.173
I know I've got this color, and
I know Butch is gonna love it.

23:54.266 --> 23:55.683
I just want to see what
Shannon has to say about it.

23:55.842 --> 23:56.934
- Dude, it's beautiful.

23:57.018 --> 23:58.352
- That's a beautiful color,
dude.

23:58.437 --> 23:59.845
- What color is this?

23:59.929 --> 24:01.522
- It's black cherry,
light on the black.

24:01.681 --> 24:02.848
- Really?
- Yeah.

24:02.932 --> 24:04.108
- Is it dry?

24:04.192 --> 24:05.684
- Well, he sprayed it yesterday,

24:05.777 --> 24:07.519
I just want to bake it
in the sun before we buff it.

24:07.604 --> 24:10.030
- It looks like it's still wet.
- Nice and shiny.

24:10.115 --> 24:13.025
- Unbelievable.
It looks like candy-candy.

24:13.118 --> 24:14.443
- Oh, yeah. It is candy.

24:14.536 --> 24:15.703
- But no pinstripes, no nothing?

24:15.862 --> 24:17.538
- Not on the frame.

24:17.622 --> 24:19.031
Most of this stuff gets all
covered up and everything,

24:19.124 --> 24:22.209
but I'm really excited
that we got a new gas tank.

24:22.368 --> 24:23.952
Brand-spanking new.

24:24.037 --> 24:27.131
- Yeah, no, I know we've tried
to fix that thing.

24:27.290 --> 24:29.124
It's just the inside of it,
it's...

24:29.209 --> 24:29.958
- It's not worth it.
- It's got that liner in it.

24:30.043 --> 24:31.302
- Yeah.

24:31.461 --> 24:33.053
- You know,
Butch was a little hesitant

24:33.213 --> 24:34.796
when we told him, like,
"Hey, you need a new gas tank,

24:34.881 --> 24:36.882
because this one's been
put through the wringer."

24:36.975 --> 24:39.226
- Once you cream a gas tank
it's creamed for life.

24:39.311 --> 24:40.728
- Well, we can't guarantee it.
- Yep.

24:40.812 --> 24:42.971
- We cannot guarantee the
inside is going to hold up.

24:43.056 --> 24:44.732
- Trying to save that other one
is great and all,

24:44.891 --> 24:46.308
it sounds great, if it was

24:46.392 --> 24:47.902
a full on restoration,
we'd commit to it.

24:47.986 --> 24:50.646
But if we can find
a brand-new gas tank

24:50.730 --> 24:53.157
and it's exactly the gas tank
that goes with bike...

24:53.316 --> 24:56.327
so the frame done,
brand-new gas tank in,

24:56.486 --> 24:58.570
all the other stuff
is ready to base,

24:58.655 --> 25:01.332
I can start doing
all the cobweb flames, dude.

25:01.416 --> 25:03.075
That's one thing
I've never done before.

25:03.168 --> 25:05.577
- Like, ghosted cobwebs?

25:05.662 --> 25:07.338
Or, like, you-can-see-them
cobwebs?

25:07.422 --> 25:09.089
- You know what?
I'm not so sure yet.

25:09.174 --> 25:10.591
I'm not sure yet.

25:10.675 --> 25:12.251
I think I want to do
the cobwebs in black.

25:12.335 --> 25:13.585
- Yeah?

25:13.670 --> 25:16.347
- And cobweb everything
but the flames.

25:16.431 --> 25:19.591
The darker color
is actually just cobwebs.

25:19.684 --> 25:21.352
From across the parking lot,
it looks like, you know,

25:21.511 --> 25:23.595
a dark cherry bike
with some red ghost--

25:23.680 --> 25:24.846
- Gotcha.

25:24.940 --> 25:26.357
- Oh, maybe I want to go
check that out,

25:26.516 --> 25:28.016
and you start looking at it,
and you're like,

25:28.101 --> 25:29.360
"Wait a minute,
these aren't ghost flames.

25:29.444 --> 25:30.861
That's straight up
cobwebs everywhere."

25:30.946 --> 25:34.198
- For some reason,
this thing is, like, bling.

25:34.282 --> 25:36.033
- Oh, yeah.
- Massive.

25:36.192 --> 25:37.201
- Pow.

25:37.360 --> 25:38.953
- Can I get it at the end
of the day?

25:39.112 --> 25:40.621
- Tomorrow, absolutely.

25:40.705 --> 25:41.872
- I'll buy you lunch.

25:42.031 --> 25:43.615
- Does it come with
a time machine?

25:43.700 --> 25:45.534
- What time machine?
It's lunch.

25:45.618 --> 25:47.119
- You'll thank me later
when you're not working

25:47.212 --> 25:48.537
with a wet frame.

25:48.621 --> 25:49.630
- Thank you.

25:49.714 --> 25:56.679
<i>[rock music]</i>

25:59.558 --> 26:01.725
- All right, start going down.

26:01.884 --> 26:03.468
We're going
to kind of step it in.

26:03.562 --> 26:06.221
- What up, fellas?
Oh, man, I came at a good time.

26:06.306 --> 26:09.308
Man, it's been all hands
on deck on this '78 Corvett.

26:09.392 --> 26:10.985
And it's going to be
magnificent.

26:11.069 --> 26:13.729
And I just got word that Bob
and the boys are about to drop

26:13.822 --> 26:15.573
in that brand-new LS3 engine.

26:15.657 --> 26:17.992
This has got to be about three
time as much engine as this car

26:18.076 --> 26:19.651
came from the factory with,
so now I'm going to head

26:19.736 --> 26:21.987
over there and check out
how it's coming out.

26:22.080 --> 26:23.414
- Hey, Danny.

26:23.573 --> 26:24.740
- What's happening?
What's happening?

26:24.824 --> 26:26.500
- Oh, not much.
- Come forward more.

26:26.585 --> 26:27.918
- Stop right here?

26:28.077 --> 26:29.086
- Yeah, that's
a good spot for you.

26:29.245 --> 26:30.662
- Absolutely, man.
I got the view.

26:30.747 --> 26:32.590
- Move her deeper into the car.
Okay, stop.

26:32.749 --> 26:33.665
- Come on down.
- And let's go down.

26:33.750 --> 26:38.587
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:38.680 --> 26:40.097
- No issues over there, Frank?

26:40.181 --> 26:42.007
- No, none at all.
- Come on, come on,

26:42.100 --> 26:43.183
come on, come on.

26:43.268 --> 26:45.102
All right, stop.
Now let's go down again.

26:45.261 --> 26:46.595
We're gonna keep
staggering it down.

26:46.679 --> 26:47.846
- Okay.

26:47.930 --> 26:49.106
- All right,
hold it right there.

26:49.265 --> 26:51.850
We need to go in
just about a little bit.

26:51.934 --> 26:53.444
- Ooh, really, really close.
- I think you--yeah.

26:53.528 --> 26:54.353
- I'm about a quarter
of an inch.

26:54.446 --> 26:55.779
Let me twist the engine.

26:55.864 --> 26:56.772
- Oh, let me move this
harness out.

26:56.856 --> 26:58.190
- Wiring harness in the way.

26:58.274 --> 27:00.200
- All right,
come down real slow.

27:00.285 --> 27:01.860
- Nice and easy.

27:01.953 --> 27:05.039
- All right, hold up.
And let's go in about an inch

27:05.198 --> 27:06.123
and right on the mount.

27:06.207 --> 27:08.283
- Straight down.
A little bit more.

27:08.368 --> 27:10.461
- Look at that.
- A little bit more.

27:10.620 --> 27:12.129
- Look at that.
- How you doing, Frank?

27:12.213 --> 27:13.797
You getting there?
- There we go.

27:13.882 --> 27:15.290
- There she goes.
- A little jiggle.

27:15.383 --> 27:16.958
- Look at that.
- Guess what.

27:17.052 --> 27:18.218
Go ahead and kill it,
because we're in.

27:18.378 --> 27:19.470
- Yep.
- Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

27:19.554 --> 27:21.046
- There she goes.
- There it is.

27:21.130 --> 27:22.723
Yeah, that final drop
right there I think.

27:22.882 --> 27:26.226
That's beautiful. Look at that.
Yeah, dude, this is wicked.

27:26.386 --> 27:29.146
LS3 wrapped in plastic.

27:29.305 --> 27:31.649
- Yes.
- This car is going to fly.

27:31.733 --> 27:33.809
Frank, what are we
putting behind this?

27:33.893 --> 27:36.395
Is it the 4L65? 4L70? 4L80?

27:36.479 --> 27:38.313
- I believe it's the 4L80, sir.
- Get down.

27:38.398 --> 27:39.898
And it fits in this tunnel.

27:39.982 --> 27:41.650
- Yes, sir. And we even have
the special shifter

27:41.734 --> 27:43.994
to go with it;
we can bolt it right in.

27:44.079 --> 27:46.246
- Dude.
- It's a style shifter.

27:46.331 --> 27:47.823
Fits in the console,
so this thing

27:47.907 --> 27:50.751
is gonna look like 1978 inside.

27:50.835 --> 27:54.421
- I love stuff that looks like
the '70s but runs modern.

27:54.580 --> 27:55.497
I mean, that's awesome.

27:55.590 --> 27:56.840
- This is gonna be dependable.

27:56.925 --> 27:58.342
He's gonna drive this
every single day.

27:58.426 --> 28:00.094
- Good Lord a'mighty.

28:00.253 --> 28:02.087
This car, I'm gonna be jealous
of this car when it goes.

28:02.171 --> 28:05.841
'78 pace car, proper colors,
done Count's Kustoms' style,

28:05.925 --> 28:09.678
but all this modern,
wicked, wicked performance.

28:09.762 --> 28:11.689
Come on.
Tear it up, gents. Tear it up.

28:11.773 --> 28:13.598
Beautiful, beautiful, beautiful.

28:13.683 --> 28:15.600
Man, I love it.
- Let's check the headers.

28:15.685 --> 28:17.602
- This car's gonna be nice.

28:17.696 --> 28:19.029
- Mounts and...

28:19.188 --> 28:20.188
- Check headers
and go from there.

28:20.273 --> 28:20.864
- All right.

28:25.787 --> 28:27.788
<i>- A couple of weeks ago
we got a call from a client</i>

28:27.872 --> 28:31.125
<i>looking to fix up his
2005 Iron Horse motorcycle.</i>

28:31.209 --> 28:32.868
<i>She was in pretty
solid shape overall</i>

28:32.952 --> 28:35.370
<i>but had some damage
to the gas tank from a fall.</i>

28:35.455 --> 28:37.131
<i>So although Butch really
wanted to keep</i>

28:37.290 --> 28:38.874
<i>the original gas tank,</i>

28:38.958 --> 28:41.051
<i>we ultimately decided
that it would be safer</i>

28:41.136 --> 28:42.553
<i>to replace that tank
with a new one.</i>

28:42.712 --> 28:44.796
<i>Of course,
Ryan did what he does best.</i>

28:44.889 --> 28:47.466
<i>He laid down a sick candy
black cherry paint job</i>

28:47.550 --> 28:50.394
<i>with some stellar artwork
to just set this baby of.</i>

28:50.478 --> 28:52.563
<i>Now that she's done,
we got Butch down here</i>

28:52.647 --> 28:54.815
to check it out, and he gave
Ryan a whole lot of freedom,

28:54.899 --> 28:58.059
but I know he's going to dig
how this thing came out.

28:58.153 --> 28:59.737
Butch, I got to talk
to you, man.

28:59.821 --> 29:02.647
I got to talk to you
about this bike.

29:02.732 --> 29:04.983
- My bike was a nice bike
before I brought it here.

29:05.076 --> 29:07.152
I was just having
paint issues with it, man.

29:07.236 --> 29:10.998
- Well, I heard you had
a little spill with it.

29:11.082 --> 29:12.741
- Why'd you ask me
about that, dude?

29:12.825 --> 29:14.752
- Yeah, man. What happened?

29:14.836 --> 29:18.747
- I T-boned a car, dude.
- Yeah.

29:18.831 --> 29:20.415
- Jacked me up, man.
- Yeah.

29:20.508 --> 29:21.750
- You know?
- It hurts.

29:21.834 --> 29:24.503
- Shattered my hip,
broke my ankle.

29:24.587 --> 29:26.671
And that was before
I went over the car.

29:26.756 --> 29:28.006
- Dude.

29:28.090 --> 29:29.674
- I said, "You know what, man?

29:29.768 --> 29:31.935
"When a cowboy falls
off of his horse, he gets up,

29:32.020 --> 29:35.764
knocks the dirt off his pants,
and gets back on the horse."

29:35.848 --> 29:39.443
- That's right.
So thank God you have survived.

29:39.527 --> 29:43.363
Anyways, there were
several things that the team

29:43.523 --> 29:45.106
went through on the bike.

29:45.191 --> 29:48.276
I appreciate you saying,
you know what?

29:48.361 --> 29:49.620
You're done messing
around with it,

29:49.704 --> 29:51.196
just want it done right.

29:51.280 --> 29:53.207
- Danny, I walked out of here
when I brought it,

29:53.291 --> 29:55.459
I walked out of here in tears.

29:55.618 --> 29:57.285
You know, I just looked
at Ryan, man...

29:57.370 --> 29:58.203
- Yeah.
- And I told him,

29:58.287 --> 30:00.964
"Ryan..."
- Yeah.

30:01.049 --> 30:02.874
- "You know what I want, man."
- Yeah.

30:02.967 --> 30:04.125
- And he looked at me,
and he shook his head,

30:04.210 --> 30:06.303
and he goes... just like that,
dude,

30:06.462 --> 30:07.888
and I said,
"That's all I needed to know."

30:07.972 --> 30:09.464
- Yep, yep.
Are you ready for this?

30:09.549 --> 30:11.883
- Yes, I am, man.

30:11.976 --> 30:13.635
- Shannon.

30:13.719 --> 30:15.479
- Bring that baby out here.

30:15.638 --> 30:18.557
- Bring out Butch's beautiful
Iron Horse.

30:18.641 --> 30:19.566
[engine turns over]

30:19.651 --> 30:20.567
- Oh, that's it.

30:20.652 --> 30:24.980
[engine revving]

30:25.064 --> 30:27.566
- Sounds ready.

30:27.650 --> 30:34.498
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:34.582 --> 30:35.907
- Son of a [bleep].

30:35.992 --> 30:38.493
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:38.578 --> 30:39.578
Oh, my God.

30:39.662 --> 30:42.756
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:42.841 --> 30:44.591
- I can't.
- Take your time.

30:44.676 --> 30:46.918
Exactly. You're right.

30:47.003 --> 30:49.346
- I don't believe this.

30:49.430 --> 30:53.183
Look at my friggin'
motorcycle, man.

30:53.342 --> 30:55.927
<i>- Man, this 2005
Iron Horse motorcycle</i>

30:56.012 --> 30:58.605
<i>gets more incredible
the closer you get.</i>

30:58.690 --> 31:00.015
<i>Shannon went over this bike</i>

31:00.099 --> 31:02.276
<i>with a fine-tooth comb repairing</i>

31:02.360 --> 31:04.853
<i>any accident damage,
rewiring the electronics,</i>

31:04.946 --> 31:06.438
<i>and dialing in that big engine.</i>

31:06.522 --> 31:09.107
<i>Now she sounds and rides
just like she did</i>

31:09.191 --> 31:11.026
<i>when she rolled off
the showroom floor.</i>

31:11.110 --> 31:12.527
<i>Then Ryan worked his magic</i>

31:12.612 --> 31:14.863
<i>and did what no one
but Ryan can do,</i>

31:14.947 --> 31:17.365
<i>a ridiculous black
cherry candy paint job</i>

31:17.450 --> 31:19.710
<i>that totally makes
the custom pinstripes</i>

31:19.869 --> 31:21.461
<i>and cobwebs pop in the sunlight.</i>

31:21.546 --> 31:23.547
<i>This bike came out so good
that I know</i>

31:23.706 --> 31:25.883
<i>when Butch hits the road
on this bad boy</i>

31:25.967 --> 31:29.210
<i>he's definitely gonna turn
some heads wherever he goes.</i>

31:29.295 --> 31:32.964
- I promise you you will never
see another one like it.

31:33.049 --> 31:34.633
I've never done that.
- Thank you, brother.

31:34.717 --> 31:38.053
- [chuckles]

31:38.137 --> 31:39.646
- Thank you, bro.
- Thank you.

31:39.805 --> 31:41.806
- I've never that before, and I
will never do it again.

31:41.891 --> 31:45.235
- Thank you.

31:45.320 --> 31:49.656
I wasn't expecting this, man,
at all.

31:49.741 --> 31:52.567
- She's never looked like this.
- No.

31:52.652 --> 31:54.912
- Shannon, take a minute
to tell Butch

31:55.071 --> 31:56.997
about everything you
went through.

31:57.081 --> 31:59.074
- Well, I mean,
you brought us a bike

31:59.158 --> 32:00.500
that needed a lot of work,
which was,

32:00.660 --> 32:01.826
you know, which was okay.

32:01.911 --> 32:03.495
- I didn't think it needed
that much work

32:03.579 --> 32:05.923
until you got to working on it.

32:06.082 --> 32:07.758
- Took this thing down
to the frame, man.

32:07.917 --> 32:10.260
- And you had carburetor
problems too, right?

32:10.345 --> 32:12.429
- Yeah, that carburetor
had, you know,

32:12.588 --> 32:14.598
it's a stuck
accelerator pump and whatnot.

32:14.682 --> 32:15.682
So I mean, right now...
- Not anymore.

32:15.767 --> 32:18.602
- It's immediate fuel.

32:18.686 --> 32:20.929
- It's going to feel like you
got two engines in there now

32:21.013 --> 32:22.439
compared to the last time
you rode it.

32:22.523 --> 32:24.024
- Was this dirty and
you cleaned it

32:24.108 --> 32:25.350
and turned it chrome?

32:25.443 --> 32:26.944
[laughter]

32:27.028 --> 32:28.436
- No.
- The tank is all fixed now,

32:28.521 --> 32:30.855
there's no pinholes,
there's no more fuel leaks,

32:30.949 --> 32:33.692
the carburetor's perfect,
the wiring's perfect.

32:33.785 --> 32:38.279
- And Shannon tracked down
one of two existing tanks.

32:38.364 --> 32:40.615
- I go, "Man, I hope
it matches up."

32:40.700 --> 32:42.283
I said, "I could tell
if it's the same tank."

32:42.368 --> 32:43.627
- Yep.
- It is.

32:43.711 --> 32:45.704
- Yep.
Ryan, talk about this paint.

32:45.797 --> 32:49.383
- Well, Butch, originally
you picked out a color

32:49.467 --> 32:50.717
out of the chip book,
and you said,

32:50.802 --> 32:52.636
"I want black cherry,

32:52.720 --> 32:55.463
but I want you
to go easy on the black."

32:55.548 --> 32:57.975
You wanted a little more red
than the black side.

32:58.059 --> 32:59.968
And then you wanted
pinstripe flames

33:00.052 --> 33:02.887
and then cobwebs
all around the flames.

33:02.972 --> 33:05.140
- The skull, man.
- That, actually,

33:05.224 --> 33:06.558
- It's awesome.

33:06.651 --> 33:07.985
I got that from the artwork
that you sent me.

33:08.144 --> 33:09.903
